		<div id="comment_body_64288018"><p>I found out in 5th grade.</p><p>We had a test of spatial reasoning. There were flat diagrams of squares with numbers and dots. We were told to match them to the image of the 3D shape they would create when folded.</p><p>It was laughably easy.</p><p>My teacher later told me I was the only one who got them all correct, and no one else was even close.</p><p>That's when I learned that I "think in pictures" while most people "think in words".</p><p><span class="substr"> </span> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thinking_in_Pictures" title="wikipedia.org">Thinking in Pictures</a> [wikipedia.org] </p></div>
